CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1960, pg. 3, reads: "Nixon - Lodge - The Committee of Democrats and Independents supporting Richard M. Nixon and Henry Cabot Lodge, candidates for President and Vice President, respectively, opened their Hill District headquarters at 2033 Centre Ave., Tuesday night. Committee members shown above are, front row, left to right: Rufus Wheeler, Mrs. Annabelle Robinson, Mrs. None Patterson, Mrs. Rachel Washington, Mrs. Ollie Wheeler, Miss Ida Buckingham.  Back row: Rev. J. C. Harris, Mrs. Bernice Chappelle, Mrs. Mamie Ellison, Mrs. Effie Williams, Dr. Bradie O. Hopper, Mrs. Viola Parker, Miss Caroll Shelton. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Rufus Wheeler, Annabelle Robinson, None Patterson, Rachel Washington, Ollie Wheeler, Ida Buckingham: back row: Rev. J. C. Harris, Bernice Chappelle, Mamie Ellison, Effie Williams, Dr. Bradie O. Hopper, Viola Parker, and Caroll Shelton, posed in Nixon - Lodge campaign office, 2033 Centre Avenue, Hill District
